cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.DS

This paper discusses the detection and mitigation of banking Trojans, which are a type of malware used by financially-motivated cybercriminals. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes the use of evolutionary computational intelligence for mitigation strategies, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The taxonomy proposed in the paper can also inform the design of software systems, which relates to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the stages of a cyber-attack, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper analyzes a dataset of banking Trojans, which relates to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
